The paper deals with computational problems in the context of abstract argumentation, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The approach presented in the paper involves algorithmic techniques and fixed-parameter tractability, which are common topics in machine learning and data mining (cs.LG) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses different semantics and frameworks, which are relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
